ity/116700695927139221', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['redpacketsecurity.com'], 'email-addr': ['RedPacketSecurity@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'UN World Food Programme (WFP) says its Gaza aid registration system was hacked. Attackers stole personal data, including names, ID numbers, phone numbers, and location details, affecting around 600,000 Palestinian households #databreach https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/un-world-food-programme-breach-affects-600-000-gaza-households/', 'publication_date': 'Sat, 06 Jun 2026 00:23:59 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@DevaOnBreaches/116700240718755430', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['UN World Food Programme (WFP) says its Gaza aid registration system was hacked. Attackers stole personal data, including names, ID numbers, phone numbers, and location details, affecting around 600,000 Palestinian households#databreach'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['bleepingcomputer.com']}}, {'title': "🛡️ If you don't fall for these extortionists' calls, they'll show up wit...📝 If they don't g...https://www.theregister.com/cyber-crime/2026/06/05/if-you-dont-fall-for-these-extortionists-calls-theyll-show-up-with-usb-sticks/5251891📰 www.theregister.com - Articles#DataBreach #Phishing", 'publication_date': 'Sat, 06 Jun 2026 00:23:59 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@bugxhunter/116700221814374509', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'artifact': [], 'autonomous-system': [], 'directory': [], 'domain-name': [], 'email-addr': [], 'email-message': [], 'file': [], 'ipv4-addr': [], 'ipv6-addr': [], 'mac-addr': [], 'mutex': [], 'network-traffic': [], 'process': [], 'software': [], 'url': [], 'user-account': [], 'windows-registry-key': [], 'x509-certificate': [], 'vulnerability': [], 'mitre': []}}, {'title': "@Lazarou Forcing everyone to dox themselves isn't going to make anything safer those identity documents have to be stored in a hackable database literally every ID verifier has been hacked multiple times since this crap started #databreach #Ageverification", 'publication_date': 'Fri, 05 Jun 2026 23:24:43 +0000', 'source': 'https://masto.nu/@CuteCatThunder/116699972690053299', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['CuteCatThunder@masto.nu', 'Lazarou@mastodon.social', 'Lazarou@mastodon.socialThe']}}, {'title': 'DATE: June 5, 2026 at 04:21PM SOURCE: HEALTHCARE INFO SECURITYDirect article link at end of text block below.@Conduent  Hack Victim Count Now Tops 62.2 Million:  Back-Office Servicer\'s #DataBreach Estimate Has More Than Doubled Since Februaryhttps://www.healthcareinfosecurity.com/conduent-hack-victim-count-now-tops-622-million-a-31900 #HIPAAHere are any URLs found in the article text: https://www.healthcareinfosecurity.com/conduent-hack-victim-count-now-tops-622-million-a-31900Articles can be found by scrolling down the page at https://www.healthcareinfosecurity.com/ under the title "Latest"-------------------------------------------------Private, vetted email list for mental health professionals: https://www.clinicians-exchange.orgHealthcare security & privacy posts not related to IT or infosec are at @HIPAABot . Even so, they mix in some infosec with the legal & regulatory information.-------------------------------------------------#security #healthcare #doctors #itsecurity #hacking #doxxing #psychotherapy #securitynews #psychotherapist #mentalhealth #psychiatry #hospital #socialwork #datasecurity #webbeacons #cookies #HIPAA #privacy #datanalytics #healthcaresecurity #healthitsecurity #patientrecords  @infosec #telehealth #netneutrality  #socialengineering', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 05 Jun 2026 20:26:47 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.clinicians-exchange.org/@rsstosecurity/116699373020739906', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["@Conduent Hack Victim Count Now Tops 62.2 Million: Back-Office